01752                 int xN, const real_t *x, int xLD, real_t *y, int yLD) const
01753 {
01754         int i, j, k, l, idx, row, col;
01755 
01756         /* clear output */
01757         for (i = 0; i < xN*xN; i++)
01758                 y[i] = 0.0;
01759 
01760         /* compute lower triangle */
01761         for (l = 0; l < icols->length; l++)
01762         {
01763                 col = icols->number[icols->iSort[l]];
01764                 idx = jd[col];
01765                 k = 0;
01766                 while (idx < jc[col+1] && k < icols->length)
01767                 {
01768                         row = icols->number[icols->iSort[k]];
01769                         if (ir[idx] == row)
01770                         {
01771                                 /* TODO: It is possible to formulate this as DSYR and DSYR2
01772                                  * operations. */
01773                                 if (row == col) /* diagonal element */
01774                                         for (i = 0; i < xN; i++)
01775                                                 for (j = i; j < xN; j++)
01776                                                         y[i*yLD+j] += val[idx] * x[i*xLD+col] * x[j*xLD+col];
01777                                 else /* subdiagonal elements */
01778                                         for (i = 0; i < xN; i++)
01779                                                 for (j = i; j < xN; j++)
01780                                                         y[i*yLD+j] += val[idx] * (x[i*xLD+col] * x[j*xLD+row] + x[i*xLD+row] * x[j*xLD+col]);
01781                                 idx++, k++;
01782                         }
01783                         else if (ir[idx] > row) k++;
01784                         else idx++;
01785                 }
01786         }
01787 
01788         /* fill upper triangle */
01789         for (i = 0; i < xN; i++)
01790                 for (j = i; j < xN; j++)
01791                         y[j*yLD+i] = y[i*yLD+j];
